RACE.FOOTNOTES: PEYTON ELIZABETH rated off the inside and edged up to be in range into the turn, shifted four wide under some coaxing into the lane, advance between rivals while being flashed the stick leaving the three sixteenths pole, moved clear a furlong out once set down, kept on under pressure through the final sixteenth and held sway. HASHTAG LUCKY quickly went clear, set the pace well off the inside, was joined from her inside nearing the turn, sparred under asking past the three eighths, wandered out to about the five path maintaining the advantage into the lane, straightened away to fight on heading to mid stretch, saw the winner get away a bit near the sixteenth pole but kept on gamely despite swapping leads to come back on some and hold down the place. CHAMPAGNE TOAST , four wide early, dropped in to about the two path mid turn, came back out through the drive and closed steadily. I CAN RUN stumbled at the break, regrouped and settled off the inside, angled six wide into the lane and rallied. HAINT BLUE lagged back while saving ground, angled three to four wide for the drive and closed between runners. GOOD PENNY saved ground under some rating, remained inside making steady progress past the quarter pole, eased out, churned on to the inside of rivals then flattened out. CONTINENTALCONGRES pulled her way forward and bid inside HASHTAG LUCKY heading to the turn, dueled around the turn and into the lane, stayed on with interest to mid stretch, could not offer more near the sixteenth marker and weakened. DRY WELL steadied at the break, lagged back, saved ground into the stretch but failed to menace. SILVER CURRENCY , four then three wide stalking the pace, was under pressure mid turn, lacked a kick nearing the lane and retreated.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LAUREL PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 51740. (PLUS UP TO 15% MBF) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $45,000, if for $36,000, allowed 4 lbs. MD-Bred and/or MD-Sired horses may waive claiming price in this race.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CIRCLE P broke alertly then was rated back off the leaders, edged up off the rail leaving the far turn, moved boldly three to four wide approaching the stretch, responded when asked inside the three sixteenths and forged past JOLLY BOSS, was given a couple taps then drew out emphatically while steadily hand ridden the final sixteenth. JOLLY BOSS pressed two wide outside a rival, moved to command near the three eighths, briefly went clear under rating mid turn, came under a ride once collared from his outside entering the lane, ceded to the winner nearing mid stretch, faded late but had enough left to save the place. FORMAL AFFAIR saved ground, steadied near the three eighths, eased out and moved up between runners into the lane, came out past mid stretch and continued on with effort. THIS IS GOOD broke outward a bit, bumped with a rival then checked, covered to advance off the rail leaving the far turn, knifed his way three to four wide between runners nearing the stretch, angled out a bit for the final furlong and kept on trying. ALBERT FINNIGAN rated inside early, eased out then was stalled behind foes mid turn, dropped in to gain past the three sixteenths, angled out then went even late. NEVER GREW UP was checked when in tight between rivals soon after the break, gained five wide outside rivals leaving the five sixteenths but failed to sustain through the final three sixteenths. HANKSDIVININGROD broke slowly, raced well back early on, swung five wide into the lane and offered some late action. RETURN FIRE , bumped at the break, moved up and stalked off the inside, was lightly steadied in upper stretch and faded. HYTECK PRINCE stumbled at the break and failed to menace. SCRAPPY T LEE , four wide pursuing, raced between foes past the five sixteenths and weakened. ROCKET DRAGON rushed up inside to take command after a sixteenth, set a pressured pace, stayed on to the head of the lane then tired. NO WORRIES , bumped leaving the gate, gave early chase between rivals and tired in upper stretch.
